CrazySexyCool: The TLC Story is a television biographical film about the R&B/Hip hop group TLC. The film stars Keke Palmer as Rozonda "Chilli" Thomas, Natia "Lil Mama" Kirkland as Lisa "Left-Eye" Lopes, and Drew Sidora as Tionne "T-Boz" Watkins. TLC goes from humble beginnings to unprecedented fame.
